  "question": "Carlos is planting a lemon tree. The tree will cost $90 to plant. Each year it will grow 7 lemons, which he can sell for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years will it take before he starts earning money on the lemon tree?",
  "prompt": "Carlos is planting a lemon tree. The tree will cost $90 to plant. Each year it will grow 7 lemons, which he can sell for $1.5 each. It costs $3 a year to water and feed the tree. How many years will it take before he starts earning money on the lemon tree?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "13",
  "generated_text": "To determine how many years it takes for Carlos to start earning money, we need to compare the **Cost** to the **Revenue** for each year.\n\n**1. Define the variables:**\n*   **Planting Cost:** $\\$90$ (one-time initial cost).\n*   **Annual Revenue per lemon:** $\\$1.50$\n*   **Annual Revenue per lemon:** $\\text{Number of lemons} \\times \\$1.50$\n*   **Annual Cost:** $\\$3$\n\n**2. Determine the number of lemons per year:**\n*   Year 1: 0 lemons (just planted)\n*   Year 2: 7 lemons\n*   Year 3: 14 lemons\n*   Year $n$: $7 \\times n$ lemons\n\n**3. Formulate the equation for \"Earning Money\":**\nCarlos starts earning money when the total revenue from selling lemons is greater than the planting cost ($\\$90$).\n$$ \\text{Total Revenue} > \\text{Planting Cost} $$\n\nThe total revenue for $n$ years (where $n > 1$) is:\n$$ \\text{Total Revenue} = n \\times (\\text{lemons per year}) \\times (\\text{price per lemon}) $$\n$$ \\text{Total Revenue} = n \\times 7 \\times 1.5 $$\n$$ \\text{Total Revenue} = 10.5n $$\n\nThe inequality to solve is:\n$$ 10.5n > 90 $$\n\n**4. Solve the inequality:**\n$$ n > \\frac{90}{10.5} $$\n\nCalculate the division:\n$$ \\frac{90}{10.5} = \\frac{900}{105} $$\nDivide numerator and denominator by 15:\n$$ \\frac{60}{7} \\approx 8.57 $$\n\n**5. Interpret the result:**\nSince $n$ must be an integer (you can't have a fraction of a year in this context), we look for the smallest integer greater than 8.57.\n*   For $n = 8$: Revenue = $8 \\times 10.5 = \\$84$. ($84 < 90$, still a loss).\n*   For $n = 9$: Revenue = $9 \\times 10.5 = \\$94.50$. ($94.50 > 90$, start earning).\n\nTherefore, it takes 9 years for the revenue to exceed the planting cost.\n\n\\boxed{9}\n",
  "pred_answer": "9",
